Curriculum Ontology: Description back to ToC

This ontology is a formal representation that captures the fundamental concepts and their relationships to one another in the field of curriculum design and implementation of the German school system.

Cross-reference for Curriculum Ontology classes, object properties and data properties back to ToC

This section provides details for each class and property defined by Curriculum Ontology.

A1 Anfängerc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0010002

Kann vertraute, alltägliche Ausdrücke und ganz einfache Sätze verstehen und verwenden, die auf die Befriedigung konkreter Bedürfnisse zielen. Kann sich und andere vorstellen und anderen Leuten Fragen zu ihrer Person stellen – z. B. wo sie wohnen, was für Leute sie kennen oder was für Dinge sie haben – und kann auf Fragen dieser Art Antwort geben. Kann sich auf einfache Art verständigen, wenn die Gesprächspartnerinnen oder Gesprächspartner langsam und deutlich sprechen und bereit sind zu helfen.
has super-classes
Femdsprachenniveau c

A2 Grundlegende Kenntnissec back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0010003

Kann Sätze und häufig gebrauchte Ausdrücke verstehen, die mit Bereichen von ganz unmittelbarer Bedeutung zusammenhängen (z. B. Informationen zur Person und zur Familie, Einkaufen, Arbeit, nähere Umgebung). Kann sich in einfachen, routinemäßigen Situationen verständigen, in denen es um einen einfachen und direkten Austausch von Informationen über vertraute und geläufige Dinge geht. Kann mit einfachen Mitteln die eigene Herkunft und Ausbildung, die direkte Umgebung und Dinge im Zusammenhang mit unmittelbaren Bedürfnissen beschreiben.
has super-classes
Femdsprachenniveau c

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000450

Documents which refer to additional resources to learn with.

additional material (BE)c back to ToC or Class ToC

Documents which refer to additional resources to learn with.

Allgemeine Hochschulreifec back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000076

The "Allgemeine Hochschulreife" is a "Schulabschluss" and the highest general education school-leaving qualification. It is awarded after grade 12 or 13, depending on the federal state and type of school, and entitles the holder to study at a university. The term "Allgemeine Hochschulreife" is used synonymously with "Abitur".
Die “Allgemeine Hochschulreife” ist ein “Schulabschluss” und der höchste allgemeinbildende Schulabschluss. Er wird je nach Bundesland und Schulart nach der Jahrgangsstufe 12 oder 13 verliehen und berechtigt zum Studium an einer Hochschule. Die “Allgemeine Hochschulreife” wird synonym zum Begriff Abitur verwendet.

Anforderungsbereichc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000802

Umfasst Repräsentationen für die drei Anforderungsbereiche. Im deutschen und österreichischen Schulsystem werden die Lernziele meist in drei Anforderungsbereiche aufgeteilt, die ein unterschiedliches Ausmaß von Eigenleistung und komplexem Denken vom Schüler erfordern. Der Anforderungsbereich I umfasst meist eine Reproduktion, Anforderungsbereich II eine Reorganisation (Umgestaltung) sowie einen Transfer (Übertragung, Anwendung) und Anforderungsbereich III Urteilsbildung, Reflexion und Problemlösung.
editorial note

Kann die Hauptpunkte verstehen, wenn klare Standardsprache verwendet wird und wenn es um vertraute Dinge aus Arbeit, Schule, Freizeit usw. geht. Bildungsgangc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000816

A "Bildungsgang" refers to a specific educational pathway that leads to a particular qualification or school-leaving certificate. This pathway includes multiple school levels, the duration of which is defined by the "Bildungsgang". It requires the achievement of a defined competence profile, which is assessed through various forms of performance evaluation. Curricula specify the content and competencies to be assessed in each subject. In the ontology, we distinguish three "Bildungsgänge" in general education: - The "Hauptschulbildungsgang", leading to the "Erste Schulabschluss"; - The "Realschulbildungsgang", leading to the "Mittlere Schulabschluss"; - The "Gymnasiale Bildungsgang", leading to the "Allgemeine Hochschulreife".
has super-classes
process c
has sub-classes
Gymnasium Track c, Hauptschule Track c, Realschule Track c
is in domain of
hat Bildungsgangniveau op
is disjoint with
school subject c, Lehrprozess c, Learning Process c, Jahrgangsstufe c, Person c, Lehrer Rolle c, Schüler Rolle c, Kompetenz c, Schulabschluss c, Niveau c, school type c, Curriculares Element c, Lehrplan c, Funktionsspezifikation c, Schulfachbezug c, Bildungsstandard (KMK) c, Organisation c

Bildungsgangniveauc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000028

The "Bildungsgangniveau" is a "Niveau" that describes the requirements within an "Bildungsgang" and characterizes the differences in performance levels between various educational tracks. It describes the depth and level of demand with which learning content and competencies are addressed within this educational track. In the ontology, a distinction is made between "Hauptschulniveau", "Realschulniveau", "Gymnasialniveau Sek I", and "Gymnasialniveau Sek II". These correspond to the basic, intermediate, and advanced requirements used in some lower secondary curricula to categorize competences. While the "Fachniveau" describes the specific requirements in a single subject within the upper secondary level of the Gymnasium track, the "Bildungsgangniveau" refers to the level of an entire educational track aimed at a specific qualification.
has super-classes
Niveau c
has sub-classes
Bildungsgangniveau (BB / BE) c, Bildungsgangniveau (BW) c, Bildungsgangniveau (BY) c, Bildungsgangniveau (HB) c, Bildungsgangniveau (HE) c, Bildungsgangniveau (HH) c, Bildungsgangniveau (MV) c, Bildungsgangniveau (NI) c, Bildungsgangniveau (NW) c, Bildungsgangniveau (RP) c, Bildungsgangniveau (SH) c, Bildungsgangniveau (SL) c, Bildungsgangniveau (SN) c, Bildungsgangniveau (ST) c, Bildungsgangniveau (TH) c, Gymnasialniveau Sek II c, Hauptschulniveau c
is in domain of
inkludiert op
is in range of
hat Bildungsgangniveau op, inkludiert op

Bildungsstandard (KMK)c back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000571

The "Bildungsstandard" is an “Information Content Entity” that describes clearly defined, binding learning objectives which learners are expected to achieve at a specific point in time. It ensures consistent quality and transparency within the education system and enables objective performance measurement. The "Bildungsstandards" adopted by the Kultusministerkonferenz (KMK) reflect general educational goals and define which competencies students should have acquired in key subject areas by a certain grade level. The "Bildungsstandards" focus on core areas of a subject and describe expected learning outcomes. The "Bildungsstandards" of the KMK represent a combination of content and output standards. They refer to the average expected performance level of students at the end of grade 4, at the point of the First School Leaving Certificate, the Intermediate School Leaving Certificate, and the General Higher Education Entrance Qualification, and are therefore considered regular standards. (cf. KMK)
has super-classes
information content entity c
is disjoint with
school subject c, Lehrprozess c, Learning Process c, Jahrgangsstufe c, Person c, Lehrer Rolle c, Schüler Rolle c, Kompetenz c, Schulabschluss c, Niveau c, school type c, Curriculares Element c, Lehrplan c, Funktionsspezifikation c, Schulfachbezug c, Organisation c, Bildungsgang c

A "Bistafach" is a "Schulfach" for which the KMK has published "Bildungsstandards". The "Bistafächer" are German, mathematics, the first foreign language (English or French), and the three natural sciences: biology, chemistry, and physics.
is equivalent to
{ Biologie (Schulfach) ni , Chemie (Schulfach) ni , Deutsch (Schulfach) ni , Englisch (Schulfach) ni , Französisch (Schulfach) ni , Mathematik (Schulfach) ni , Physik (Schulfach) ni }
has super-classes
school subject c

Kann ein breites Spektrum anspruchsvoller, längerer Texte verstehen und auch implizite Bedeutungen erfassen. CE-Bereichc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000349

A “CE-Bereich” is a “Curriculares Element”. A “CE-Bereich” can be superordinate or subordinate to other “CE-Bereichen”. The element serves to structure curricula and educational standards by grouping “CE-Kompetenzspezifikationen” and/or “CE-Lerninhalte” under a common content focus, which is defined by the “CE-Bereich”.
editorial note
Mögliche Properties: - Titel - Ordnungsnummer - Beschreibung - Stundenzahl - Jahrgangsstufe
has super-classes
Curriculares Element c

A "CE-Fragment" is a "Curriculares Element" with a structuring function. It is used to delineate a specific context within a curriculum or educational standard, such as chapters or thematic divisions.

CE-Hinweisc back to ToC or Class ToC

A “CE-Hinweis”’ is a “Curriculares Element” that contains supplementary information or suggestions on a “CE-Bereich”, a “CE-Lerninhalt” or a “CE-Kompetenzspezifikation”. CE-Kompetenzspezifikationc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000263

A “CE-Kompetenzspezifikation” is a “Curriculares Element” that describes a competence. It usually contains an operator and begins with “The students [...]” or “The learners [...]” for example. The ontology distinguishes between “CE-Kompetenzspezifikation” and “Kompetenz”: A competence is understood as the ability of a learner to apply knowledge and skills to solve problems (cf. KMK). In contrast to competence, which is anchored in the learner as an ability or skill, the “CE-Kompetenzspezifikation” is the description of this competence within the framework of a curriculum or educational standard.
is equivalent to
Curriculares Element c and (inverse hat Teil op some CE-Bereich c) and (hat Funktion op value Kompetenzbeschreibungsfunktion ni)
has super-classes
Curriculares Element c
has sub-classes
Fach- und Lernbereichsübergreifende Kompetenzspezifikation c, Fachbezogene Kompetenzspezifikation c

CE-Lerninhaltc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000332

A “CE-Lerninhalt” is a “curricular element” that describes a learning content in the form of specific topics. The “CE-Lerninhalt” provides the content basis for the preparation of school lessons. Competencies can be acquired on the basis of the “CE-Lerninhalt”. A “CE-Lerninhalt” can contain another “CE-Lerninhalt”, but no other element (such as e.g. “CE-Bereich” or “CE-Kompetenzspezifikation”).
is equivalent to
Curriculares Element c and (inverse hat Teil op some CE-Lerninhalt c or CE-Bereich c) and (hat Funktion op value Lerninhaltsbeschreibungsfunktion ni)
has super-classes
Curriculares Element c

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000845

Die Progresssion ist Teil einer Kompetenz-Spezifikation oder eines Lerninhalts. Sie beschreibt genau den Teil, der je nach Niveau variabel ist. Jede Progessionssstufe hat eine eigene Beziehung zu einer Niveauspezifikation.
Example 
Wenn die Komptenz "Lesen" ist, könnten Progressionen sein: "Worte einzeln lesen", "Mit Hilfe (Finger, Stäbchen, Lineal) lesen.", "Flüssig lesen"
has super-classes

Curriculares Elementc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000261

A “Curriculares Element” is an information content entity used to describe the components of a curriculum or educational standard. In the ontology, the "Curriculares Element" serves as a superordinate category to structure the components that describe the content and competencies to be acquired within a curriculum or educational standard. A “Curriculares Element” can also have a function that defines its purpose within the curriculum in more detail. This allows the state-specific components of the curricula to be mapped, as common functions can be assigned to them. Subclasses of the “Curriculares Element” that are not state-specific are labelled with the prefix ‘CE-’.
editorial note
Wir haben 'Curriculares Element' als Bezeichnung gewählt, weil die vorherige Bezeichnung 'Lehrplan Element' zu sehr auf Lehrpläne einschränkt. Es sollen auch Bindungsstandards beschrieben werden, daher würde 'Lehrplan Element' nicht gut passen.
has super-classes
information content entity c
has sub-classes
CE-Bereich c, CE-Fragment c, CE-Hinweis c, CE-Kompetenzspezifikation c, CE-Lerninhalt c, CE-Progressionsstufe c, CE-Verweis c, Element (BB) c, Element (BE) c, Element (BW) c, Element (BY) c, Element (Bista) c, Element (HB) c, Element (HE) c, Element (HH) c, Element (MV) c, Element (NI) c, Element (NW) c, Element (RP) c, Element (SH) c, Element (SL) c, Element (SN) c, Element (ST) c, Element (TH) c, Niveaustufe (BE/BB) c
is in domain of
hat Beschreibung op, hat Niveau op, hat Niveaustufe op, hat Nummer op, hat Titel op
is disjoint with
school subject c, Lehrprozess c, Learning Process c, Jahrgangsstufe c, Person c, Lehrer Rolle c, Schüler Rolle c, Kompetenz c, Schulabschluss c, Niveau c, school type c, Lehrplan c, Funktionsspezifikation c, Schulfachbezug c, Bildungsstandard (KMK) c, Organisation c, Bildungsgang c

dispositionc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000016

(Elucidation) A disposition b is a realizable entity such that if b ceases to exist then its bearer is physically changed & b's realization occurs when and because this bearer is in some special physical circumstances & this realization occurs in virtue of the bearer's physical make-up
Is defined by
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/bfo.owl
Example 
an atom of element X has the disposition to decay to an atom of element Y
certain people have a predisposition to colon cancer
children are innately disposed to categorize objects in certain ways.
the cell wall is disposed to filter chemicals in endocytosis and exocytosis
An atom of element X has the disposition to decay to an atom of element Y; the cell wall is disposed to transport cellular material through endocytosis and exocytosis; certain people have a predisposition to colon cancer; children are innately disposed to categorize objects in certain ways
has super-classes
realizable entity c
has sub-classes

is in range of
has disposition op
is disjoint with
role c

Erster Schulabschlussc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000079

The "Erste Schulabschluss" is a "Schulabschluss" and represents the first general education school-leaving qualification. It is awarded after grade 9 or 10, depending on the federal state and type of school. In the federal states, the "Erste Schulabschluss" has various designations: - Erster allgemeinbildender Schulabschluss (HH, NW, SH) - Hauptschulabschluss (BW, HE, NI, SL, SN, ST, TH) - Berufsbildungsreife (BB, BE, HB) - Berufsreife (MV, RP) - Erfolgreicher Abschluss der Mittelschule (BY)
has super-classes

Fachniveauc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000265

The "Fachniveau" is a "Niveau". It refers to the level of requirements for a specific subject in upper secondary education ("Sekundarstufe II") and indicates whether a "Curriculares Element" is assigned to a "Grundkurs" or a "Leistungskurs". The two “Fachniveaus” differ in the complexity and depth of instruction, as well as in the scope of content and the performance expectations. While the "Bildungsgangniveau" describes the level of an entire educational track aimed at a specific qualification, the "Fachniveau" refers to the specific requirements of a subject within the Gymnasium track of upper secondary education.
has super-classes
Niveau c
has sub-classes
Grundkursniveau c, Leistungskursniveau c

Femdsprachenniveauc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0010001

The "Fremdsprachenniveau" is a "Niveau". It corresponds to the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR), which systematizes foreign language proficiency into six levels from A1 (beginner) to C2 (near-native proficiency). The "Fremdsprachenniveau" indicates the extent to which learners can understand, speak, read, and write the language, and serves as a basis for comparison within educational qualifications and international certifications.
has super-classes
Niveau c
has sub-classes
A1 Anfänger c, A2 Grundlegende Kenntnisse c, B1 Fortgeschrittene Sprachverwendung c, B2 Selbständige Sprachverwendung c, C1 Fachkundige Sprachkenntnisse c, C2 Annähernd muttersprachliche Kenntnisse c

fiat linec back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000142

(Elucidation) A fiat line is a one-dimensional continuant fiat boundary that is continuous
Example 
The Equator; all geopolitical boundaries; all lines of latitude and longitude; the median sulcus of your tongue; the line separating the outer surface of the mucosa of the lower lip from the outer surface of the skin of the chin
has super-classes
continuant fiat boundary c
is disjoint with
fiat surface c, fiat point c

fiat object partc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000024

(Elucidation) A fiat object part b is a material entity & such that if b exists then it is continuant part of some object c & demarcated from the remainder of c by one or more fiat surfaces
Example 
The upper and lower lobes of the left lung; the dorsal and ventral surfaces of the body; the Western hemisphere of the Earth; the FMA:regional parts of an intact human body
has super-classes
material entity c

fiat pointc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000147

(Elucidation) A fiat point is a zero-dimensional continuant fiat boundary that consists of a single point
Example 
The geographic North Pole; the quadripoint where the boundaries of Colorado, Utah, New Mexico and Arizona meet; the point of origin of some spatial coordinate system
has super-classes
continuant fiat boundary c
is disjoint with
fiat line c, fiat surface c

fiat surfacec back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000146

(Elucidation) A fiat surface is a two-dimensional continuant fiat boundary that is self-connected
Example 
The surface of the Earth; the plane separating the smoking from the non-smoking zone in a restaurant

is disjoint with

generically dependent continuantc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000031

b is a generically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant that g-depends_on one or more other entities. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [074-001])
A continuant that is dependent on one or other independent continuant bearers. For every instance of A requires some instance of (an independent continuant type) B but which instance of B serves can change from time to time.
(Elucidation) A generically dependent continuant is an entity that exists in virtue of the fact that there is at least one of what may be multiple copies which is the content or the pattern that multiple copies would share
Is defined by
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/bfo.owl
Example 
The entries in your database are patterns instantiated as quality instances in your hard drive. The database itself is an aggregate of such patterns. When you create the database you create a particular instance of the generically dependent continuant type database. Each entry in the database is an instance of the generically dependent continuant type IAO: information content entity.
the pdf file on your laptop, the pdf file that is a copy thereof on my laptop
the sequence of this protein molecule; the sequence that is a copy thereof in that protein molecule.
The pdf file on your laptop; the pdf file that is a copy thereof on my laptop; the sequence of this protein molecule; the sequence that is a copy thereof in that protein molecule; the content that is shared by a string of dots and dashes written on a page and the transmitted Morse code signal; the content of a sentence; an engineering blueprint
has super-classes
continuant c
has sub-classes
information content entity c
is in domain of
is concretized as op
is in range of
concretizes op
is disjoint with
independent continuant c, specifically dependent continuant c, independent continuant c, specifically dependent continuant c

Gymnasium Trackc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000815

The "Gymnasiale Bildungsgang" is a "Bildungsgang". It aims to prepare learners for the "Abitur" and subsequent university studies. Typically, this educational track extends to grade 12 or 13 and concludes with the "Allgemeine Hochschulreife" (Abitur), which grants access to universities and higher education institutions. The curriculum content for the "Gymnasiale Bildungsgang" is more academically demanding and theoretical than that of the "Hauptschul-" or "Realschulbildungsgang". The "Gymnasiale Bildungsgang" does not necessarily have to be completed at a Gymnasium; it can also be pursued at “Gesamt- oder Gemeinschaftsschulen” offering schooling at the Gymnasium level with the goal of achieving the "Allgemeine Hochschulreife".
is equivalent to
(Bildungsgang c and ((hat Bildungsgangniveau op some Gymnasialniveau Sek I c) or (hat Bildungsgangniveau op some Gymnasialniveau Sek II c))) or (für Schulart op value Gymnasium ni)
has super-classes
Bildungsgang c

Hauptschule Trackc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000813

The "Hauptschulbildungsgang" is a "Bildungsgang". It primarily prepares learners for vocational training and direct entry into the workforce. It typically concludes after grade 9 or 10 with the "Erste Schulabschluss". The focus is on a basic general education, combined with practical and career-oriented elements. In addition to core subjects (German, mathematics), learners also acquire technical or manual skills. The "Erste Schulabschluss" provides access to vocational training programs and, with appropriate performance, may also allow admission to higher educational tracks (e.g., "Realschulbildungsgang", "Gymnasialer Bildungsgang").
is equivalent to
Bildungsgang c and (hat Bildungsgangniveau op some Hauptschulniveau c)
has super-classes
Bildungsgang c

independent continuantc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000004

b is an independent continuant = Def. b is a continuant which is such that there is no c and no t such that b s-depends_on c at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [017-002])
A continuant that is a bearer of quality and realizable entity entities, in which other entities inhere and which itself cannot inhere in anything.
b is an independent continuant =Def b is a continuant & there is no c such that b specifically depends on c or b generically depends on c
Is defined by
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/bfo.owl
Example 
a chair
a heart
a leg
a molecule
a spatial region
an atom
an orchestra.
an organism
the bottom right portion of a human torso
the interior of your mouth

Jahrgangsstufec back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000009

A "Jahrgangsstufe" is an "Information Content Entity". It encompasses all classes and courses in which learners progress together through a specific stage of their educational journey. A "Jahrgangsstufe" refers to a systematic grouping of learners and indicates the phase of their educational path, defining the competencies and learning content intended for them. Upon completion of a school year, learners transition to the next "Jahrgangsstufe". In curricula, the "Jahrgangsstufe" serves as an organizational element that structures teaching content in an age-appropriate manner. Depending on the type of school and the federal state, "Jahrgangsstufen" may be referred to differently (e.g., "Klassenstufen") or grouped together, such as in the form of double year groups.
has super-classes
information content entity c

Kompetenzc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000013

A “competence” is a characteristic that a person either already possesses or acquires in the course of a learning process. It is the ability of a learner to apply knowledge and skills to solve problems (cf. KMK). The ontology distinguishes between “competence” and “CE competence specification”: In contrast to the “CE competence specification”, which describes a “competence” within the framework of a curriculum or educational standard, the “competence” is anchored as an ability or skill in the learner himself.

disposition c

Lehrplanc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000438

A curriculum is an information content entity that comprises a systematic compilation of curricular elements. It bindingly defines the skills and learning content that students should acquire in a particular subject, grade, type of school or educational level in a federal state. A curriculum is always specific to the educational policy of a federal state and differs from the nationwide educational standards that are published by the Kultusministerkonferenz (KMK). They can serve as the basis for the development of specific curricula in the federal states. In addition to the binding requirements, the curriculum often also contains information on the didactic and methodological design of lessons as well as cross-references to related and interdisciplinary skills and content from other school subjects. Depending on the federal state, curricula can have different names.
has super-classes
information content entity c
has sub-classes

Niveauc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000037

The "Niveau" is an “information content entity”. It denotes a categorization of the extent to which one or more specific characteristics are expressed. In the educational context, the "Niveau" refers to the level, complexity, depth, or degree of difficulty of a learning content or a competence defined in a curriculum or educational standard. The "Niveau" indicates the requirements placed on learners in terms of knowledge, skills, and abilities, and can be differentiated into areas such as levels of demand, educational track level, subject level, and foreign language level. It does not indicate the grade or school level of the learners.
has super-classes
information content entity c
has sub-classes
Anforderungsbereich c, Bildungsgangniveau c, Fachniveau c, Femdsprachenniveau c
is in range of
hat Niveau op
is disjoint with
school subject c, Lehrprozess c, Learning Process c, Jahrgangsstufe c, Person c, Lehrer Rolle c, Schüler Rolle c, Kompetenz c, Schulabschluss c, school type c, Curriculares Element c, Lehrplan c, Funktionsspezifikation c, Schulfachbezug c, Bildungsstandard (KMK) c, Organisation c, Bildungsgang c

objectc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030

(Elucidation) An object is a material entity which manifests causal unity & is of a type instances of which are maximal relative to the sort of causal unity manifested
Example 
An organism; a fish tank; a planet; a laptop; a valve; a block of marble; an ice cube
has super-classes
material entity c
has sub-classes
Person c

object aggregatec back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027

(Elucidation) An object aggregate is a material entity consisting exactly of a plurality (≥1) of objects as member parts which together form a unit
Example

Realschule Trackc back to ToC or Class ToC

The "Realschulbildungsgang" is a "Bildungsgang". It provides a solid general education with an emphasis on practical content. It leads to the "Mittlere Schulabschluss" after grade 10. This qualification allows access to vocational training and, with sufficient achievement, may also enable admission to the "Gymnasialer Bildungsgang". Instruction is less theoretical than at the Gymnasium but more demanding than in the "Hauptschulbildungsgang".

A realizable entity the manifestation of which brings about some result or end that is not essential to a continuant in virtue of the kind of thing that it is but that can be served or participated in by that kind of continuant in some kinds of natural, social or institutional contexts.
(Elucidation) A role b is a realizable entity such that b exists because there is some single bearer that is in some special physical, social, or institutional set of circumstances in which this bearer does not have to be & b is not such that, if it ceases to exist, then the physical make-up of the bearer is thereby changed

school typec back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000111

A "Schulart" is a “information content entity”. It is a form of school characterized by specific features that define its organizational structure, pedagogical orientation, duration of the educational stage, and the intended school-leaving qualifications. Depending on the education system and the federal state, it may include different names and concepts such as Grundschule, Gymnasium, Realschule, Hauptschule, Gesamtschule, vocational school ("Berufsschule"), or special needs school ("Förderschule"). In everyday language, "Schulart" and "Schulform" are often used synonymously.
Example 
Die Schulform einer Schule kann sich ändern. Deshalb werden die Schulformen als "Kategorie" der Funktionen einer Schule definiert. So  ist es möglich, dass einer konkreten Schule mehrere Schulformen zugeordnet werden können, und sodass jede Schulform an einen Zeitpunkt geknüpft werden kann.

https://www.echo-online.de/lokales/kreis-gross-gerau/landkreis-gross-gerau/aenderung-der-schulform-war-ueberfaellig-4054079

:schuleTreburSchulform2 :konkretisiertSchulform :Hauptschule .

:schuleTreburSchulform3 :konkretisiertSchulform :Gesamtschule

:schuleTrebur :hatSchulformfunktion :schuleTreburSchulform3 .

Schulabschlussc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000019

A "Schulabschluss" is a "process boundary". It is an officially recognized educational qualification obtained at the end of a specific educational track. It certifies the successful completion of a school career and serves as proof of qualification for further education or entry into the workforce. "Schulabschlüsse" vary in their requirements, entitlements, and designations depending on the type of school and the federal state. Common general education "Schulabschlüsse" in Germany include the "Erste Schulabschluss", the "Mittlere Schulabschluss", and the "Allgemeine Hochschulreife" (Abitur). Additional qualifications may also be awarded depending on the federal state and educational track.
has super-classes
process boundary c
has sub-classes
Fachabitur c, Förderschulabschluss c
is in range of
endet mit Abschluss op
is disjoint with

Schulstufec back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000020

The "Schulstufe" is an “information content entity”. It refers to a specific phase of the school career in which learners are expected to achieve certain goals according to the requirements of the education system. "Schulstufen" provide learners with a structured learning path, with pedagogical and didactic requirements adapted to the respective age groups. Each "Schulstufe" includes designated grade levels depending on the educational track and federal state. It differs from: the "Bildungsgang" (which refers to the type of qualification, e.g., "Gymnasialer Bildungsgang" or "Realschulbildungsgang"), the "Bildungsgangniveau" (which describes the level of an educational track), and the "Fachniveau" (which describes the depth and scope of a specific subject in upper secondary education). In general education, we distinguish between the "Primarstufe" (also called Grundschule), the "Sekundarstufe I", and the "Sekundarstufe II" (also known as the upper secondary level or "gymnasiale Oberstufe"). Note: The "Primarbereich", "Sekundarbereich I", and "Sekundarbereich II" are instances of the class "Schulstufe".
has super-classes
information content entity c
has sub-classes
Gymnasiale Oberstufe c, Orientierungsstufe c
has members
Primarbereich ni, Sekundarbereich I ni, Sekundarbereich II ni
is disjoint with
school subject c, Jahrgangsstufe c

specifically dependent continuantc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000020

b is a specifically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant & there is some independent continuant c which is not a spatial region and which is such that b s-depends_on c at every time t during the course of b’s existence. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [050-003])
A continuant that inheres in or is borne by other entities. Every instance of A requires some specific instance of B which must always be the same.
b is a specifically dependent continuant =Def b is a continuant & there is some independent continuant c which is not a spatial region & which is such that b specifically depends on c
Is defined by
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/bfo.owl
Example 
Reciprocal specifically dependent continuants: the function of this key to open this lock and the mutually dependent disposition of this lock: to be opened by this key
of one-sided specifically dependent continuants: the mass of this tomato
of relational dependent continuants (multiple bearers): John’s love for Mary, the ownership relation between John and this statue, the relation of authority between John and his subordinates.
the disposition of this fish to decay
the function of this heart: to pump blood
the mutual dependence of proton donors and acceptors in chemical reactions [79
the mutual dependence of the role predator and the role prey as played by two organisms in a given interaction
the pink color of a medium rare piece of grilled filet mignon at its center
the role of being a doctor
the shape of this hole.
the smell of this portion of mozzarella
(with multiple bearers) John's love for Mary; the ownership relation between John and this statue; the relation of authority between John and his subordinates
(with one bearer) The mass of this tomato; the pink colour of a medium rare piece of grilled filet mignon at its centre; the smell of this portion of mozzarella; the disposition of this fish to decay; the role of being a doctor; the function of this heart to pump blood; the shape of this hole
has super-classes
continuant c
has sub-classes
quality c, realizable entity c
is in domain of
concretizes op, inheres in op, specifically depended on by op, specifically depends on op
is in range of
bearer of op, has characteristic op, is concretized as op, specifically depended on by op, specifically depends on op
is disjoint with
independent continuant c, generically dependent continuant c, independent continuant c, generically dependent continuant c

three-dimensional spatial regionc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000028

(Elucidation) A three-dimensional spatial region is a whole consisting of a spatial volume together with zero or more spatial volumes which may have spatial regions of lower dimension as parts
Example 
A cube-shaped region of space; a sphere-shaped region of space; the region of space occupied by all and only the planets in the solar system at some point in time
has super-classes
spatial region c
is disjoint with
two-dimensional spatial region c, zero-dimensional spatial region c, one-dimensional spatial region c

Unterrichtseinheitspezifikationc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000505

Ein Data Item, dass die thematische und inhaltliche Einheit des Unterrichts ausdrückt. Es kann entweder feste Zeitspannen, die Unterrichtsstunden meinen (z.B. 45 Minuten), oder sie umfasst mehrere solcher Unterrichtsstunden, um ein zusammenhängendes Stoffgebiet zu behandeln.
Example 
Soll z.B. ausgedrückt werden, dass der Unterricht 6 Einheiten à 45 Minuten enhält kann folgendes Muster verwendet werden:

:unterricht_1 'mem:described by' :ue_1 .
ue_1 a mem:Unterrichtseinheitsspezifikation .
ue_1 'mem:hat Wert' "6"^^xsd:decimal .
ue_1 'mem:hat Teil' zs_1 .
zs_1 a mem:Zeitpezifikation .
zs_1 'mem:hat Wert' "45"^^xsd:decimal .
zs_1 'mem:hat Einheit' qudt:Min .
has super-classes
data item c

Sachunterricht Primar
has super-classes

Vorschlag und Hinweis (SL)c back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0002239

editorial note
Kommt vor im Fach Mathematik in der Gemeinschaftsschule und im Gymnasium in der Sek I und Sek II. Und im Fach Deutsch in der Primarstufe, in der Sek I in der Gemeinschaftsschule und in der Sek II in der gymasialen Oberstufe. Ist oft nochmal untergliedert. In Deutsch untergliedert in z.B.: "Zur Unterrichtsgestaltung", ""Zu Methoden und Arbeitstechniken", "Zur Aufgabenstellung", "Zu Leistungsfeststellung". "Hinweise" kommt auch oft (fast immer) in den Fächern Englisch und Naturwissenschfaten/Physik als Überschrift für weitere Kategorien vor (auf derselben ebene wie Kompetenzerwartungen).

characteristic ofop back to ToC or Object Property ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052

a relation between a specifically dependent continuant (the characteristic) and any other entity (the bearer), in which the characteristic depends on the bearer for its existence.
Note that this relation was previously called "inheres in", but was changed to be called "characteristic of" because BFO2 uses "inheres in" in a more restricted fashion. This relation differs from BFO2:inheres_in in two respects: (1) it does not impose a range constraint, and thus it allows qualities of processes, as well as of information entities, whereas BFO2 restricts inheres_in to only apply to independent continuants (2) it is declared functional, i.e. something can only be a characteristic of one thing.
Example 
this fragility is a characteristic of this vase
this red color is a characteristic of this apple

has characteristics: functional

has sub-properties
disposition of op, function of op, quality of op, role of op
is inverse of
has characteristic op

concretizesop back to ToC or Object Property ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000059

A relationship between a specifically dependent continuant or process and a generically dependent continuant, in which the generically dependent continuant depends on some independent continuant in virtue of the fact that the specifically dependent continuant or process also depends on that same independent continuant. Multiple specifically dependent continuants or processes can concretize the same generically dependent continuant.
Example 
A journal article is an information artifact that inheres in some number of printed journals. For each copy of the printed journal there is some quality that carries the journal article, such as a pattern of ink. The quality (a specifically dependent continuant) concretizes the journal article (a generically dependent continuant), and both depend on that copy of the printed journal (an independent continuant).
An investigator reads a protocol and forms a plan to carry out an assay. The plan is a realizable entity (a specifically dependent continuant) that concretizes the protocol (a generically dependent continuant), and both depend on the investigator (an independent continuant). The plan is then realized by the assay (a process).
has sub-properties
konkretisiert Lehrplan op, konkretisiert Schulart op
has domain
process c or specifically dependent continuant c
has range
generically dependent continuant c
is inverse of
is concretized as op

Paraphrase of definition: a relation between an independent continuant and a process, in which the process takes place entirely within the independent continuant

http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/bfo.owl

hat Schulfachop back to ToC or Object Property ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000537

Wird verwendet, um Etwas einem Fach oder einem Fach mit besonderem "Bezug" (z.B. Zweite-Fremdsprache) zuzuordnen.
editorial note
wird üblicherweise am Lehrplan verwendet; kann ggf. auch an Kompetenzbereichen/Kompetenzspezifikation bzw. Themenbereichen/Themen verwendet werden, z.B. bei Lehrplänene die sich auf mehrere Fächer beziehen
Example 
Gegeben sind:

:sf_1 a :Schulfach .
:sf_1 sameAs ex:Englisch .

Bspl 1: "Lehrplanelement :lpe_1 bezieht sich auf Schulfach Englisch"

:lpe_1 :hat_schulfach :sf_1 .

Bspl 2: "Lehrplanelement :lpe_1 bezieht sich auf Schulfach Englisch als Zweite-Fremdsprache"

:lpe_2 :hat_schulfach :bezug_1 .
:bezug_1 :hat_schulfach :sf_1 .
:bezug_1 a :Zweite_Fremdsprache .

Anmerkung: Durch die Property Chain wird in Beispiel 2 durch den Reasoner das folgende Tripel automatisch ergänzt:

:lpe_2 :hat_schulfach :sf_1 .

described by op
has range
school subject c or Schulfachbezug c
has sub-property chains
hat Schulfach op o hat Schulfach op

is concretized asop back to ToC or Object Property ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000058

A relationship between a generically dependent continuant and a specifically dependent continuant or process, in which the generically dependent continuant depends on some independent continuant or process in virtue of the fact that the specifically dependent continuant or process also depends on that same independent continuant. A generically dependent continuant may be concretized as multiple specifically dependent continuants or processes.
Example 
A journal article is an information artifact that inheres in some number of printed journals. For each copy of the printed journal there is some quality that carries the journal article, such as a pattern of ink. The journal article (a generically dependent continuant) is concretized as the quality (a specifically dependent continuant), and both depend on that copy of the printed journal (an independent continuant).
An investigator reads a protocol and forms a plan to carry out an assay. The plan is a realizable entity (a specifically dependent continuant) that concretizes the protocol (a generically dependent continuant), and both depend on the investigator (an independent continuant). The plan is then realized by the assay (a process).
has domain
generically dependent continuant c
has range
process c or specifically dependent continuant c
is inverse of
concretizes op

occurs inop back to ToC or Object Property ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000066

b occurs_in c =def b is a process and c is a material entity or immaterial entity& there exists a spatiotemporal region r and b occupies_spatiotemporal_region r.& forall(t) if b exists_at t then c exists_at t & there exist spatial regions s and s’ where & b spatially_projects_onto s at t& c is occupies_spatial_region s’ at t& s is a proper_continuant_part_of s’ at t
Paraphrase of definition: a relation between a process and an independent continuant, in which the process takes place entirely within the independent continuant
b occurs in c =Def b is a process or a process boundary & c is a material entity or site & there exists a spatiotemporal region r & b occupies spatiotemporal region r & for all time t, if b exists at t then c exists at t & there exist spatial regions s and s' where b spatially projects onto s at t & c occupies spatial region s' at t & s is a continuant part of s' at t
Is defined by
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/bfo.owl
Example 
A process of digestion occurs in the interior of an organism; a process of loading artillery rounds into a tank cannon occurs in the interior of the tank
has domain
occurrent c
process c or process boundary c
has range
independent continuant c
site c or material entity c
is inverse of
contains process op, environs op
has sub-property chains
part of op o occurs in op
occurs in op o part of op

quality ofop back to ToC or Object Property ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080

a relation between a quality and an independent continuant (the bearer), in which the quality specifically depends on the bearer for its existence
This relation is modeled after the BFO relation of the same name which was in BFO2, but is used in a more restricted sense - specifically, we model this relation as functional (inherited from characteristic-of). Note that this relation is now removed from BFO2020.
Example 
this red color is a quality of this apple
has super-properties
characteristic of op
is inverse of
has quality op

realizesop back to ToC or Object Property ToC

IRI: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000055

Paraphrase of elucidation: a relation between a process and a realizable entity, where there is some material entity that is bearer of the realizable entity and participates in the process, and the realizable entity comes to be realized in the course of the process
(Elucidation) realizes is a relation between a process b and realizable entity c such that c inheres in some d & for all t, if b has participant d then c exists & the type instantiated by b is correlated with the type instantiated by c
Is defined by
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/iao.owl
Example 
this disease course realizes this disease
this investigation realizes this investigator role
this shattering realizes this fragility
A balding process realizes a disposition to go bald; a studying process realizes a student role; a process of pumping blood realizes the pumping function of a heart
has domain
process c
has range
realizable entity c
is inverse of
has realization op

Erweitertes Anforderungsniveau (HB)ni back to ToC or Named Individual ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000034

Bezeichnet das Niveau, das an Gesamt-, Regel-, Sekundar-, u.ä. Schulen sowie Gymnasien bzgl. der Klassenstufen kleiner 11 gilt und das einem gymnasialen Bildungsgang entspricht. D.h. die Schülerinnen und Schüler verfolgen einen Bildungsgang, der zum Abitur führt, sind aber noch nicht in der gymnasialen Oberstufe (Klassenstufe 11/12/13).

Fragmentfunktionni back to ToC or Named Individual ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000627

Ist eine Stukturierungsfunktion, die ein Lehrplanelement inne haben kann. Ein Lehrplanelement, das diese Funktion inne hat, identifiziert einen Teil des Lehrplan. Die Art des Lehrplanteils muss nicht näher spezifizert sein. Wenngleich diese Definition auch auf Kompetenzbereiche oder Themenfelder anwendbar ist, ist sie ihnen ausdrücklich nicht gleichzusetzen, über- oder unterzuordnen. Die Funktion soll also nur verwendet werden, für Elemente, die nicht über die anderen Strukturierungsfunktionen spezifiziert werden können.
belongs to
Strukturierungsfunktion c
has facts
example ap "Funktion eines Lehrplanelements, das z.B. ein Kapitel, einen Absatz, oder bestimmte Seiten des Lehrplans identifiziert."@de

Gemeinschaftsschuleni back to ToC or Named Individual ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000112

Eine “Gemeinschaftsschule” ist eine “Schulart” in BW, BE, SL, SN, ST, SH und TH, die sich durch folgende Merkmale von anderen Schularten unterscheidet: - Schulstufe: Sekundarstufe I, in BE, SN, TH auch Primarbereich, in BW, BE, SL, SN, ST, SH, TH auch Sekundarstufe II - Jahrgangsstufen: 5-10, in BE, SN und TH 1-12/13 in BW, SL und ST 5-12/13, - Abschlüsse: Erster und Mittlerer Schulabschluss und die Allgemeine Hochschulreife
belongs to
school type c
has facts
von Bundesland op Thüringen ni
von Bundesland op Sachsen ni
von Bundesland op Berlin ni
von Bundesland op Baden-Württemberg ni
von Bundesland op Sachsen-Anhalt ni
von Bundesland op Schleswig-Holstein ni
von Bundesland op Saarland ni
entspricht KIM Schulart ap s09 ni

Oberschuleni back to ToC or Named Individual ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000238

Eine “Oberschule” ist eine “Schulart” in BB, HB, NI und SN, die sich durch folgende Merkmale von anderen Schularten unterscheidet: - Schulstufe: Sekundarbereich I, in SN auch Primar, in HB auch Sekundarbereich II - Jahrgangsstufen: 5-10, in SN 1-10 (s. Besonderheiten), in HB 5-13 - Abschlüsse: Erster und Mittlerer Schulabschluss, in HB auch die Allgemeine Hochschulreife - Besonderheiten: Oberschule + in SN mit verbundener Grundschule
belongs to
school type c
has facts
von Bundesland op Niedersachsen ni
von Bundesland op Sachsen ni
von Bundesland op Bremen ni
von Bundesland op Brandenburg ni
entspricht KIM Schulart ap s07 ni

Orientierungsstufeniveau (MV)ni back to ToC or Named Individual ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/LP_0000102

Bezeichnet das Niveau, das an Gesamt-, Regel-, Sekundar-, u.ä. Schulen sowie Gymnasien bzgl. der Klassenstufen kleiner 11 gilt und das einem gymnasialen Bildungsgang entspricht. D.h. die Schülerinnen und Schüler verfolgen einen Bildungsgang, der zum Abitur führt, sind aber noch nicht in der gymnasialen Oberstufe (Klassenstufe 11/12/13).

Realschulniveau c
Hauptschulniveau c

Any class lacking "ready_for_release" should be considered likely to change place in hierarchy, have its definition refined, or be obsoleted in the next release. SWRL rules

  • Rule #1
  • Rule #2
  • Rule #3
  • Rule #4

Rule #1back to ToC or SWRL ToC

disposition c(?d) , has characteristic op(?e,?d) -> has disposition op(?e,?d)

Rule #2back to ToC or SWRL ToC

quality c(?d) , has characteristic op(?e,?d) -> has quality op(?e,?d)

Rule #3back to ToC or SWRL ToC

role c(?d) , has characteristic op(?e,?d) -> has role op(?e,?d)

Rule #4back to ToC or SWRL ToC

function c(?d) , has characteristic op(?e,?d) -> has function op(?e,?d)

Legend back to ToC

c: Classes
op: Object Properties
dp: Data Properties
ni: Named Individuals
ep: External Properties
